in Brennglas, um die nationalsozialistischen und die faschistischen Vorstellungen von Imperium, Besatzung und Machtdurchsetzung zu untersuchen. Die Autorin analysiert auf einer breiten Quellenbasis aus deutschen, italienischen, serbischen und kroatischen Archiven die deutsche und die italienische Besatzungspolitik und insbesondere auch das Verhalten gegenüber der Lokalbevölkerung.  aThe "Independent State of Croatia," occupied by Germany and Italy, is a laboratory for investigating Nazi and Fascist notions of empire, occupation, and the enforcement of power. For the first time, Sanela Schmid draws on a broad set of sources from German, Italian, and post-Yugoslav archives to examine the two occupation regions that divided Croatia until the Italian capitulation.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aHistory (General). 0aHistory of Central Europe. 0aLaw of nations. 0aPolitical theory. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zCroatia. 4aFaschismus. 4aJugoslawien. 4aNationalsozialismus. 4aUnabhängiger Staat Kroatien. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  aFascism.  aIndependent State of Croatia.  aNational Socialism.  aYugoslavia.2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831106203680 cprintz978311062031340uhttps://doi.o